# Lab: Finding the Market

> You're walking through a small town and you need to find the local market. You stop someone on the street to ask for directions. One person is the lost visitor, the other is a helpful local.

## Roles

A: Local
  You know the town well and are happy to help — give directions like you actually would, casually

B: Visitante (Visitor)
  You're exploring the town and need to find the market — you don't know the area at all

## Turns

B: Stop someone and politely ask for directions to the market
   (Get their attention first, then ask)
   - Disculpe | Excuse me
   - ¿Dónde queda el mercado? | Where is the market?
   - ¿Cómo llego al mercado? | How do I get to the market?
   hint: Disculpe, ¿cómo llego al mercado?

A: Acknowledge them and start giving directions
   (Be friendly and give the first step)
   - Sí, claro | Yes, of course
   - Camina derecho | Walk straight
   - por esta calle | down this street
   hint: Sí, claro. Camina derecho por esta calle.

B: Confirm you understand and ask how far
   (Make sure you're following)
   - ¿Derecho por aquí? | Straight this way?
   - ¿Está lejos? | Is it far?
   hint: ¿Derecho por aquí? ¿Está lejos?

A: Say it's close and give the next direction
   (Reassure them and continue)
   - No, está cerquita | No, it's really close
   - Camina dos cuadras | Walk two blocks
   - Da vuelta a la izquierda | Turn left
   hint: No, está cerquita. Camina dos cuadras y da vuelta a la izquierda.

B: Repeat back to confirm — two blocks then left
   (Echo what they said to make sure)
   - ¿Dos cuadras y a la izquierda? | Two blocks and to the left?
   - ¿En el semáforo? | At the traffic light?
   hint: ¿Dos cuadras y a la izquierda? ¿En el semáforo?

A: Confirm and give a landmark
   (Help them recognize when they've arrived)
   - Sí, en el semáforo | Yes, at the traffic light
   - Lo vas a ver | You'll see it
   - Está enfrente de la iglesia | It's across from the church
   hint: Sí, en el semáforo. Lo vas a ver, está enfrente de la iglesia.

B: Thank them and confirm — across from the church
   (Show gratitude)
   - Enfrente de la iglesia | Across from the church
   - Perfecto | Perfect
   - Muchas gracias | Thank you very much
   hint: Enfrente de la iglesia, perfecto. Muchas gracias.

A: You're welcome and wish them well
   (Be warm about it)
   - De nada | You're welcome
   - Ahí mero lo encuentra | You'll find it right there
   - ¡Suerte! | Good luck!
   hint: De nada, ahí mero lo encuentra. ¡Suerte!

B: Say goodbye warmly
   (Leave on a good note)
   - Muy amable | Very kind
   - ¡Gracias! | Thanks!
   - Hasta luego | See you later
   hint: Muy amable, ¡gracias! Hasta luego.

A: Say goodbye
   (Casual and friendly)
   - ¡Provecho! | Enjoy! (at the market — wishing good shopping)
   - Hasta luego | See you later
   hint: ¡Hasta luego!

## Tips

- "¿Dónde queda?" is more natural than "¿Dónde está?" for asking about buildings and places in Mexico.
- "Cerquita" (the diminutive of "cerca") makes you sound warmer and more natural — Mexicans love diminutives.
- "Ahí mero" is extremely common — it means "right there" with emphasis, like "that's exactly where it is."
- When someone gives you directions, repeat them back — it shows you're listening and gives them a chance to correct you.
- Practice this lab twice: once following the hints, then again asking for a different place (la farmacia, el banco, la plaza).
